    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think we're trying to constrain the amount of custom syntax we maintain, and as macros are not a very widely used feature, I'd be wary of adding more complexity. So I'd suggest that you build what you want [as an extension](http://ipython.readthedocs.io/en/stable/config/extensions/index.html#writing-extensions). We can always evaluate integrating it into IPython once it's out there.\n"
